{
  "name": "Thought Provoker",
  "type": "feat",
  "img": "icons/magic/symbols/runes-star-magenta.webp",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Category: Genjutsu </p><p>Prerequisite: Level 4+ </p><p>Each illusion you manifest, grants you the insight into thoughts and feelings of those you mentally assault.</p><p> You gain the following benefits: </p><p>• Increase your Wisdom or Charisma score by 1, to a maximum of 20 </p><p>• When a creature would fail the saving throw of a Genjutsu you cast that requires an Intelligence saving throw, you can ask one question, telepathically that the target unconsciously answers with 5 words or less.</p><p>• When a creature would fail the saving throw of a Genjutsu you cast that requires a Wisdom saving throw, you become aware if the target creature feels if they are enjoying the combat or if they feel like they are forced to by another creature, entity or force.</p><p>• When a creature would fail the saving throw of a Genjutsu you cast that requires a Charisma saving throw, the target finds it difficult to lie or withhold its true feelings verbally until the end of its next turn.</p><p></p>",
